folder: 56th Avenue & Corner of 92nd St., Queens, NY
text:
Fifty-sixth Avenue, at the S.W. corner of 92nd Street, showing three views of the house of T. Manwaring from 1852-1860. S. Manwaring was the owner in 1873: A florist Beckman occupied it in 1923. It was demolished in November 1933.

March 1923
View 2: June 1925
View 3: May 1929.

Eugene L. Armbruster Collection
